# Proxima Project Rules for Antigravity

## ⚡ CRITICAL: Agent Workflow

**BEFORE writing ANY code:**

1. **READ** `.agents/workflow.md` - This defines our entire process
2. **FOLLOW** the design-first workflow:
   ```
   Design Agent → User Approval → Frontend Agent → Done
   ```
3. **NEVER** skip the design phase
4. **ALWAYS** wait for user approval before implementing

---

## 🎨 Design System: Neobrutalism

**This is MANDATORY for all UI. No exceptions.**

### Core Principles
- **Bold Borders:** 3px minimum, solid black (#1A1A1A)
- **Vibrant Colors:** High saturation, high contrast
- **Hard Shadows:** `4px 4px 0px #000` (NO blur)
- **Sharp Corners:** 0-4px border-radius maximum
- **Heavy Typography:** 700-900 font-weight for headings

### Color Palette
```css
--primary: #FF6B6B;      /* Coral red - main actions */
--secondary: #4ECDC4;    /* Teal - secondary actions */
--accent: #FFE66D;       /* Yellow - highlights */
--black: #1A1A1A;        /* Text, borders */
--white: #FFFFFF;        /* Backgrounds */
--gray: #F7F7F7;         /* Secondary backgrounds */
```

### Typography
```css
--font: 'Inter', sans-serif;
--heading-weight: 700-900;
--body-weight: 400-500;
```

### Shadows (Hard, No Blur)
```css
--shadow-sm: 2px 2px 0px #000;
--shadow-md: 4px 4px 0px #000;
--shadow-lg: 6px 6px 0px #000;
```

**Reference:** `.agents/design.agent.md` for complete specifications

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
.agents/
├── workflow.md              ← START HERE for new features
├── design.agent.md          ← Design specifications
├── frontend.agent.md        ← Implementation rules
├── AGENTS.md                ← System overview
├── QUICK_REFERENCE.md       ← Cheat sheet
├── HOW_TO_USE.md            ← Usage guide
└── designs/
    ├── DESIGN_SPEC.md       ← Current active design
    └── archive/

frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── api.ts               ← API client (USE THIS)
│   ├── socket.ts            ← Socket client (USE THIS)
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── pages/           ← Page components
│   │   ├── components/      ← Reusable components
│   │   └── context/         ← React context
│   └── types/               ← TypeScript types

server/
├── src/routes/              ← All API endpoints
└── prisma/schema.prisma     ← Database schema
```

---

## 🚀 How to Use This Agent System

### Starting a New Feature

**User says:** "Create the login page"

**You (Antigravity) respond:**

1. **Acknowledge and start Design Agent:**
   ```
   🎨 Starting Design Agent phase...
   
   Reading .agents/design.agent.md...
   Creating neobrutalism design for login page...
   ```

2. **Create design specification:**
   - ASCII wireframe
   - Color palette (hex codes)
   - Typography specs
   - All components needed
   - All states (hover, active, disabled, loading, error)
   - Responsive behavior
   
3. **Save to:** `.agents/designs/login-page-design.md`

4. **Present to user:**
   ```
   📄 Created: .agents/designs/login-page-design.md
   
   Key features:
   - [List main design elements]
   
   Please review. Reply "approved" to proceed to implementation.
   ```

5. **WAIT for user approval** ⛔

6. **After approval, start Frontend Agent:**
   ```
   ✅ Design approved!
   💻 Starting Frontend Agent phase...
   
   Reading DESIGN_SPEC.md...
   Implementing components...
   ```

7. **Implement following `.agents/frontend.agent.md`**

---

## 💻 Implementation Rules

### TypeScript
- ✅ STRICT mode - NO `any` types
- ✅ Define interfaces for all props
- ✅ Use proper type imports

### Backend Integration
- ✅ ALWAYS use `frontend/src/api.ts` functions
- ✅ NEVER create new fetch calls
- ✅ Handle loading, error, success states
- ✅ Test with backend running

### Socket.IO
- ✅ Use `frontend/src/socket.ts` for real-time
- ✅ Clean up listeners on unmount
- ✅ Handle connection states

### Component Structure
```tsx
// 1. Imports
import { API_FUNCTION } from '@/api';

// 2. Types
interface ComponentProps { ... }

// 3. Component
export default function Component(props: ComponentProps) {
  // State
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  
  // Effects
  useEffect(() => { ... }, []);
  
  // Handlers
  const handleSubmit = async () => { ... };
  
  // Render states
  if (loading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;
  if (error) return <ErrorBanner message={error} />;
  if (!data) return <EmptyState />;
  
  return <MainContent />;
}
```

### Neobrutalism Tailwind Classes
```tsx
// Primary Button
className="
  bg-neo-primary text-neo-black font-bold
  border-3 border-neo-black
  px-6 py-3
  shadow-neo-md
  hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-neo-lg
  transition-all duration-150
"

// Input Field
className="
  w-full border-3 border-neo-black
  bg-neo-white px-4 py-3
  focus:border-neo-primary focus:outline-none
"

// Card
className="
  border-3 border-neo-black
  bg-neo-white p-6
  shadow-neo-md
"
```

