## ✅ Quality Checklist

### Before Marking Design Complete
- [ ] Neobrutalism style applied (bold borders, vibrant colors, hard shadows)
- [ ] ASCII wireframe included
- [ ] All colors specified with hex codes
- [ ] All typography defined (font, size, weight)
- [ ] All components listed
- [ ] All states described (hover, active, disabled, loading, error, empty)
- [ ] Responsive behavior specified (desktop/tablet/mobile)
- [ ] Saved to `.agents/designs/[name]-design.md`

### Before Marking Implementation Complete
- [ ] Design followed exactly (95%+ fidelity)
- [ ] Zero TypeScript errors
- [ ] No `any` types
- [ ] All API endpoints integrated
- [ ] All error states handled
- [ ] Loading states implemented
- [ ] Success feedback added (toasts, messages)
- [ ] Socket.IO integrated (if real-time needed)
- [ ] Mobile responsive
- [ ] Tested with backend running
- [ ] No console errors

---

## 📞 When to Ask User

### Design Phase - Ask When:
- Uncertain about feature requirements
- Need clarification on user flow
- Want to confirm color preferences
- Design scope is ambiguous

### Implementation Phase - Ask When:
- Design spec is unclear
- API endpoint missing (offer to create stub)
- Backend integration fails (500 errors)
- Design has accessibility issues (contrast)
- Scope is ambiguous

### NEVER:
- ❌ Guess the design intent
- ❌ Change design without approval
- ❌ Skip error handling
- ❌ Leave `any` types
- ❌ Commit broken code
- ❌ Start coding without DESIGN_SPEC.md

---

## 🔧 Quick Reference

### API Usage Pattern
```typescript
import { authAPI, classAPI, sessionAPI } from '@/api';

// Login
const response = await authAPI.login({ email, password });

// Create Class
const response = await classAPI.create({ name, subject, description });

// Start Session
const response = await sessionAPI.start(sessionId);
```

### Socket Usage Pattern
```typescript
import { socketEvents, socketListeners } from '@/socket';

// Emit
socketEvents.joinRoom({ roomId, name, role });

// Listen
socketListeners.onUserJoined((data) => { ... });
```

### State Management Pattern
```typescript
const [state, setState] = useState({
  loading: false,
  error: null as string | null,
  data: null as DataType | null,
});
```

---

## 🚫 Common Mistakes to Avoid

| Mistake | Correction |
|---------|------------|
| Starting code without design | STOP → Create DESIGN_SPEC.md first |
| Soft shadows `shadow-lg` | Use hard shadows `shadow-neo-md` |
| Rounded corners `rounded-lg` | Use `rounded-none` or `rounded-sm` |
| Thin borders `border` | Use `border-3` or `border-4` |
| Muted colors `text-gray-500` | Use `text-neo-black` |
| `any` types in TypeScript | Define proper interface |
| No error handling | Wrap API calls in try/catch |
| No loading state | Add skeleton loaders |
| Untested with backend | Always test integration |

